Summary: 
Notre Dame of Marbel High School was founded right after World War II by Rev. Francis McSorley, OMI. Over the decades, it evolved significantly, coming under the control of the Marist Brothers in 1951, opening its college department in 1955, and eventually achieving university status in 1992. Key academic expansions included establishing a graduate school in 1967 and a law school around 2018-2019. The university has been guided by numerous presidents since 1952, starting with Bro. Herbert Daniel Dumont and currently led by Bro. Paterno C. Corpus. The current principals for the basic education departments are Leann Jester Rosali (Senior High) and Allan Sumadic (Elementary and Junior High). This extracted information directly satisfies the user's request for the university's history and a list of its leaders.
